{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 01:05:02.665702", "event": "llm_end", "text": "**Anomaly detected**\n\nAll routers that should be *receiving* the 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.0.0/30 prefixes from the spine layer are instead advertising those prefixes with **their own IP address as the next‑hop**.  \nIn other words, the spine and super‑spine routers are propagating routes that point back to themselves.\n\n| Router | Prefix | Next‑hop shown | Expected next‑hop |\n|--------|--------|----------------|-------------------|\n| **spine_router_0_0** | 10.0.0.0/24 | 172.16.0.33 (self) | 172.16.0.0 (leaf) |\n| **spine_router_0_0** | 10.0.0.0/30 | 172.16.0.33 (self) | 172.16.0.0 (leaf) |\n| **spine_router_0_1** | 10.0.0.0/24 | 172.16.0.41 (self) | 172.16.0.2 (leaf) |\n| **spine_router_0_1** | 10.0.0.0/30 | 172.16.0.41 (self) | 172.16.0.2 (leaf) |\n| **super_spine_router_0** | 10.0.0.0/24 | 172.16.0.7 (self) | 172.16.0.5 (leaf) |\n| **super_spine_router_0** | 10.0.0.0/30 | 172.16.0.7 (self) | 172.16.0.5 (leaf) |\n\nThe same pattern appears for the 10.1.x.x prefixes on the spine routers, but the most obvious problem is the self‑next‑hop on the 10.0.0.0/24 and /30 routes.\n\n**Root cause**\n\nThe spine and super‑spine routers are advertising routes with the *next‑hop‑self* attribute (or a mis‑configured BGP neighbor that causes the router to use its own IP as the next hop).  \nBecause the leaf routers receive these self‑originated routes, they will try to reach the spine via the spine’s own interface, creating a routing loop and preventing traffic from reaching the leafs.\n\n**Faulty routers**\n\n- `spine_router_0_0`\n- `spine_router_0_1`\n- `super_spine_router_0`\n\n(Leaf routers are receiving the correct routes; the problem originates in the spine layer.)\n\n**Recommendation**\n\n1. Verify the BGP neighbor configuration on each spine router.  \n2. Remove any `next-hop-self` command that is applied to the 10.0.0.0/24 and /30 prefixes.  \n3. Ensure that the spine routers are advertising the leaf‑originated routes with the leaf’s IP as the next hop (e.g., `172.16.0.0` for `spine_router_0_0`, `172.16.0.2` for `spine_router_0_1`).  \n4. After correcting the neighbor configuration, redistribute the routes again and confirm that the BGP tables no longer contain self‑next‑hop entries.", "generation_info": {"model": "gpt-oss:20b", "created_at": "2025-12-12T01:05:01.969224279Z", "done": true, "done_reason": "stop", "total_duration": 29188828093, "load_duration": 73256719, "prompt_eval_count": 8160, "prompt_eval_duration": 6750821964, "eval_count": 2317, "eval_duration": 22128692201, "model_name": "gpt-oss:20b"}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8160, "output_tokens": 2317, "total_tokens": 10477}}
